01:07.200 --> 01:10.400
- What do we got?
- D.O.A. Somebody chopped his head off.

01:10.400 --> 01:13.000
The guy's in his boxer shorts
propped up in a chair.

01:13.000 --> 01:15.600
His head's facedown in his own lap.

01:15.600 --> 01:18.100
The doorman says the tenant's a male
in his mid 40s, which fits...

01:18.100 --> 01:21.200
but I didn't let him look
at the D.O.A.'s head.

01:21.100 --> 01:23.700
- I was afraid to disturb the body before you got here.
- There's no other body?

01:23.600 --> 01:25.700
- No. -
Hey. - Hey.

01:25.700 --> 01:28.200
- What do we got?
- One D.O.A.

01:28.100 --> 01:31.400
Forty-year-old white guy.
Head cut off.

01:32.800 --> 01:35.600
This cop over here, she looks like
she's ready to change careers.

01:37.200 --> 01:40.300
Why don't you come on and run this for us.

01:40.300 --> 01:42.300
In there?

01:42.300 --> 01:44.300
Yeah. That'd be good.

01:52.400 --> 01:54.400
Watch where you step.

02:00.700 --> 02:03.100
Uh, an anonymous female
calls the precinct...

02:03.100 --> 02:05.800
says someone might be hurt
in this apartment.

02:05.800 --> 02:08.600
Me and my partner come over, knock,
tried the door when there was no answer.

02:08.500 --> 02:11.100
It's unlocked.
When we come in, that's what we see.

02:11.100 --> 02:13.200
- Who covered him up?
- My partner.

02:16.700 --> 02:18.900
All right.
Let's see what we got here.

02:23.900 --> 02:26.300
You don't often encounter
this method of suicide.

02:28.300 --> 02:30.700
What's the name of that kid's story,
Ichabod Crane?

02:30.700 --> 02:33.100
The Legend of Sleepy Hollow.

02:33.100 --> 02:35.500
The Headless Horseman.

02:35.400 --> 02:37.800
I thought that was
about Notre Dame.

02:40.700 --> 02:44.200
Officer McGuire, you could do us a favor.
You could send the doorman up.

02:49.200 --> 02:51.700
She'll be okay.

02:51.600 --> 02:54.500
Hmm. Let's see his mug.

02:54.500 --> 02:57.100
Oh...

03:02.600 --> 03:04.600
He don't look much happier
in that photograph.

03:07.300 --> 03:10.400
Hope he didn't wanna
get buried wearing a hat.

04:17.300 --> 04:19.200
It's Mr. Reese.
That's definite.

04:19.200 --> 04:22.000
Yeah. Gotta contact his mother.

04:21.899 --> 04:25.000
You figure the fatal weapon
for some type of kitchen knife?

04:24.900 --> 04:29.900
You know, when I first came up, Mr. Pelacanos,
you said you had some information for me.

04:29.800 --> 04:33.300
- Oh, if you want, you can call me Gus.
- What's your information, Gus?

04:33.200 --> 04:35.500
Firstly, his length of residency...

04:35.400 --> 04:38.300
Mr. Reese lived in the building
two years, nine months.

04:38.300 --> 04:40.900
Keep to himself type person,
but very nice and polite.

04:40.900 --> 04:44.200
The man was a professor at N. Y.U. University.
I'm not sure what subject...

04:44.100 --> 04:48.100
but you could tell looking at him
that he was an educated and intelligent man.

04:48.100 --> 04:51.500
Is this background information on Mr. Reese,
or is there something related to the crime?

04:51.300 --> 04:53.700
Not passing judgment-
Occasionally I would see Mr. Reese...

04:53.700 --> 04:57.900
- in company with various guys, late teens, early 20s.
- Students?

04:57.800 --> 05:01.700
These weren't collegiate types, no.
They were mostly Spanish.

05:01.600 --> 05:05.000
- Light-skinned blacks.
- So forget college, huh?

05:05.000 --> 05:08.600
Oh, these were street-type individuals, Detective.
Or what you would call a hustler type.

05:08.500 --> 05:10.500
You figure Mr. Reese
was having sex with these guys?

05:10.400 --> 05:13.200
Not passing judgment, I would work up
that investigative angle, yeah.

05:13.200 --> 05:15.900
When was the last time
you saw him with one of these guys?

05:15.900 --> 05:19.800
Three, four weeks back, Mr. Reese
was in the company of a Spanish kid...

05:19.600 --> 05:21.600
whose name is on the tip
of my tongue...

05:21.500 --> 05:24.800
I'm looking at him right now in my mind-
which Mr. Reese introduced me.

05:24.800 --> 05:27.100
Nobody last night?
Last few days?

05:27.100 --> 05:30.200
- No, sir.
- All right, thanks.

05:30.200 --> 05:32.400
You intend on working up
that investigative angle?

05:33.600 --> 05:35.700
Yeah, right.
We're gonna look into that possibility.

05:35.800 --> 05:38.500
Happy to provide it.
And that kid's name is gonna come to me.

05:38.400 --> 05:41.100
You got my card there, right?

05:41.100 --> 05:43.200
- So, you remember, you give me a call.
- Right. Right.

05:43.100 --> 05:44.900
- Good-lookin' kid.
- Mm-hmm.

05:51.700 --> 05:54.700
Yeah, New York City
Gay Defense League.

05:54.600 --> 05:56.900
Uh-huh.
I'll make sure he...

05:58.400 --> 06:02.200
Sir, he will get the message.
I can't say when he'll return the call.

06:02.100 --> 06:06.000
All right.
You're welcome.

06:06.000 --> 06:08.700
- I'm sorry.
- That's okay. Can I speak to a detective, please?

06:08.600 --> 06:10.600
Excuse me.
You're Vanessa Del Rio.

06:10.700 --> 06:13.400
Right. I've been getting
harassing phone calls at home.

06:13.400 --> 06:16.300
I knew it was you.
I said to myself, 'Hey, wait a minute.

06:16.200 --> 06:18.200
- That's a celebrity there."
- Where should I know you from?

06:18.200 --> 06:22.400
She's sort of a famous performer
in the field of adult entertainment, Donna.

06:22.300 --> 06:25.500
- Films.
- Interesting.

06:25.400 --> 06:28.200
I got this buddy, Miss Del Rio,
to this day, he's still nuts about you.

06:28.200 --> 06:30.900
That's cool. Uh, who do I speak to
about these harassing phone calls?

06:30.900 --> 06:33.000
Well, I'm your man.
I'm-I'm a detective.

06:33.000 --> 06:35.400
I'm Detective Martinez.
How you doin'?

06:35.400 --> 06:38.000
Not too great 'cause of these friggin' calls
I'm getting at home.

06:37.900 --> 06:41.000
Yeah. All right. Well, why don't we go
in the coffee room. We'll talk about it.

06:45.400 --> 06:47.100
Lieutenant...

06:47.100 --> 06:50.500
you got several calls from the head
of the New York City Gay Defense League.

06:50.400 --> 06:52.900
- About Simone's homicide?
- Uh, he wouldn't say...

06:52.800 --> 06:54.800
but he was very persistent
that you call him back.

06:54.700 --> 06:58.000
Hey, boss, I think we found the murder weapon-
butcher knife in a towel.

06:57.900 --> 07:00.000
- Thrown down the garbage chute.
- Any direction on a perp?

07:00.000 --> 07:03.200
Well, the doorman said that the D.O.A.
Used to bring home male hustlers.

07:03.200 --> 07:06.300
N.Y.U. Professor
getting hit in the heinie.

07:06.200 --> 07:09.000
- I'm gonna grab a radio.
- There was a message on the answering machine...

07:08.900 --> 07:12.700
from the mother, talking about some
dangerous guy who was staying at the apartment...

07:12.700 --> 07:16.600
telling the D.O.A. That he either needs
to get the guy outta there or get out himself.

07:16.500 --> 07:20.200
- You reach out to the mother?
- We got her address, so we're gonna make notification.

07:20.100 --> 07:23.500
Gay professor gets decapitated.
This one's gonna get hot.

07:23.500 --> 07:26.000
- You got that phone number?
- Mm-hmm.

07:25.900 --> 07:28.200
Diane, could you,
uh, voucher this?

07:28.200 --> 07:30.600
Sure. Can I get you a cup of coffee
on your way out?

07:33.900 --> 07:37.800
So, uh, tell me about
this harassment, Miss Del Rio.

07:37.800 --> 07:41.000
Some creep keeps leaving
messages on my machine...

07:40.900 --> 07:42.900
telling me he wants to screw me.

07:42.800 --> 07:46.000
That one of these days I'm gonna belong to him.
All kinds of sick stuff.

07:45.900 --> 07:48.700
- Any idea who it might be?
- Every time I pick up the phone...

07:48.600 --> 07:50.900
and say, Who the hell is this?"
He just hangs up.

07:51.000 --> 07:53.000
And how often does he call?

07:53.000 --> 07:56.200
I've got about 15 messages
on tape in the last two months.

07:56.100 --> 07:58.400
And you don't recognize the voice?

07:58.500 --> 08:01.300
No. So last week I filed a complaint
with the Annoying Calls...

08:01.200 --> 08:03.900
- The Annoyance Calls Bureau.
- Yeah, so they're trapping my calls.

08:03.900 --> 08:06.400
They know who it is. They won't tell me.
They say I need a detective...

08:06.400 --> 08:09.100
- to contact them for phone calls.
- I can help you with that.

08:09.100 --> 08:12.400
You know, I've got a 1-900
fantasy voice mail line...

08:12.400 --> 08:15.700
$3.99 a minute, this jerk can say
whatever the hell he wants.

08:15.600 --> 08:20.500
But, see, that's Vanessa,
this is Anna Maria.

08:20.400 --> 08:22.700
- I know the difference.
- Anna Maria, huh?

08:24.000 --> 08:26.400
- Anna Maria what?
- Sanchez.

08:26.400 --> 08:29.200
Sanchez.
That's a pretty name.

08:29.200 --> 08:31.400
Hmm.

08:31.300 --> 08:33.299
Thank you very much.

08:49.900 --> 08:51.800
- Margaret Reese?
- Yes?

08:51.800 --> 08:55.100
New York Police.
I'm Detective Sipowicz.

08:55.100 --> 08:57.700
- This is Detective Simone.
- What is it?

08:57.700 --> 09:00.500
We're very sorry, but there's been
an accident involving your son, Daniel.

09:01.700 --> 09:03.800
I'm sorry, but your son's dead.

09:12.200 --> 09:14.600
We're very sorry for your loss, ma'am.

09:14.600 --> 09:17.100
What sort of accident?
Did he wreck the car?

09:20.400 --> 09:25.200
Your son was the victim
of a homicide, Mrs. Reese.

09:26.300 --> 09:28.900
This would never have happened
if he'd stayed here.

09:28.900 --> 09:30.700
You mean if he would have
stayed here last night?

09:30.800 --> 09:34.000
No, if he hadn't moved away
and left me alone.

09:33.900 --> 09:36.700
I knew there were people
who would take advantage of him.

09:36.700 --> 09:39.400
Are you thinking
of someone in particular...

09:39.400 --> 09:41.600
- who would have harmed your son?
- No.

09:41.600 --> 09:44.600
- Did you call Daniel last night, ma'am?
- Yes.

09:44.500 --> 09:47.400
'Cause there was a message on his answering
machine from a woman who sounded like you...

09:47.400 --> 09:51.200
who mentioned someone being
there in the apartment with him.

09:51.100 --> 09:53.800
And that you feel like
this other person oughta leave.

09:53.700 --> 09:56.500
Last week, Daniel told me
that he was letting a fella stay there...

09:56.500 --> 09:59.000
for a day or two,
who was down on his luck.

09:59.000 --> 10:01.600
Daniel is like that, you see.

10:01.600 --> 10:03.500
Yesterday I called.
This was a full week later.

10:03.600 --> 10:07.700
I'm not an intrusive
or a butting-in type of mother.

10:07.600 --> 10:12.000
And this man answered the phone.
He was still there.

10:11.900 --> 10:14.800
When I asked him how much longer
he planned to stay, he became abusive.

10:14.800 --> 10:18.200
- He- He was cursing me.
- Excuse me. About what time was this yesterday?

10:18.200 --> 10:21.000
In the morning.
After that, I called Daniel at the university...

10:21.000 --> 10:24.200
and asked him when
that person was getting out.

10:24.100 --> 10:27.600
Daniel said that he planned
on trying to make him leave last night.

10:27.600 --> 10:29.900
This person,
do you know his name?

10:29.900 --> 10:32.300
Daniel said it was a former student of his.
He never mentioned a name.

10:32.300 --> 10:35.100
Former student. Did you ever meet him?
See what he looks like?

10:35.000 --> 10:38.200
- No.
- From the conversation where he was cursing you...

10:38.200 --> 10:40.800
what do you remember
about his voice?

10:40.800 --> 10:43.700
Did he have a foreign accent?

10:43.600 --> 10:46.000
- Did he sound black? White?
- I couldn't tell.

10:46.100 --> 10:48.200
Mrs. Reese, did you call
the 15th Precinct this morning...

10:48.200 --> 10:50.200
to check for trouble
in your son's apartment?

10:50.100 --> 10:52.200
No. I was waiting
for him to call me back.

10:54.000 --> 10:56.900
- Do you have Daniel's car?
- I'm sorry?

10:56.800 --> 11:00.300
The Oldsmobile. It's registered in his name,
but we paid for it together.

11:00.200 --> 11:02.300
Do you know where it is?
I'd like to have it.

11:02.300 --> 11:05.100
Uh, we could find out
and let you know.

11:05.000 --> 11:08.000
- I wonder if it's been stolen.
- If you could give us the license plate...

11:08.000 --> 11:10.400
it might turn out helpful
in finding who did this.

11:10.400 --> 11:12.500
I'll write it down for you.

11:19.700 --> 11:21.700
How was Daniel murdered?

11:24.100 --> 11:28.500
Believe me...

11:28.400 --> 11:32.000
being a parent, I hate to have to
tell you something like this...

11:31.900 --> 11:35.100
but you'll need to know
for identification purposes.

11:35.100 --> 11:40.200
Your son was stabbed very badly
in the region of the neck.

11:40.000 --> 11:43.300
The knife went pretty much
right through.

11:43.300 --> 11:46.500
Are you telling me his head was cut off?
That he was decapitated?

11:49.000 --> 11:51.500
Mrs. Reese, we are...

11:51.400 --> 11:56.400
We are terribly sorry,
but it is better if you hear it now.

11:58.300 --> 12:04.100
Yes, it's good to know
in dealing with the funeral arrangements.

12:21.100 --> 12:24.300
Hey, Detective, I remember the kid.
This is Joey Suarez.

12:24.300 --> 12:27.900
You guys wanna talk to me
about Professor Reese?

12:27.900 --> 12:30.700
Uh, yeah. I'll tell you what. Why don't you
get started with Detective Sipowicz.

12:30.700 --> 12:33.300
- I got a couple of phone calls to make.
- Come on. You want some coffee?

12:33.300 --> 12:35.200
Yeah. All right.

12:37.100 --> 12:40.300
Gus, I said if you
thought of a name, call us.

12:40.300 --> 12:43.700
Oh, I saved you a step.
This kid, he moves furniture.

12:43.600 --> 12:47.000
And I saw him unloading
his truck over on Houston.

12:46.900 --> 12:48.800
What'd you tell this kid?

12:48.800 --> 12:51.200
Just how Mr. Reese got
his head cut off last night.

12:51.200 --> 12:53.300
Did you describe any details
of the crime scene?

12:53.400 --> 12:56.400
Hey, I absolutely tell you,
Detective, from his reaction...

12:56.200 --> 12:59.100
this Joey definitely
was not involved.

12:59.100 --> 13:01.900
All right, I'll talk to him. I want you
to sit on this bench right here, Gus.

13:01.800 --> 13:04.900
- You want me to wait until he's done?
- I want you to sit on the bench.

13:04.900 --> 13:07.400
- Hi, Vanessa. Come on in.
- Excuse me.

13:07.300 --> 13:09.900
Yeah.

13:09.900 --> 13:12.000
Good to see you again.

13:13.900 --> 13:16.000
Do you know a Richard Hart?

13:16.100 --> 13:18.200
Rick Hart?
Is that who's doing this?

13:18.200 --> 13:21.800
- That's my information.
- He's this guy I see at all my personal appearances.

13:21.600 --> 13:25.200
Just a little average guy
that says how much he likes my work.

13:25.200 --> 13:27.600
I've seen him in Philly, Baltimore,
all over the place.

13:27.600 --> 13:30.200
A lot of people follow you
from town to town?

13:30.200 --> 13:33.400
Some of them travel in their business.
I thought he was just a big fan.

13:33.400 --> 13:35.700
This Rick Hart, he never behaved strangely
at one of your appearances?

13:35.700 --> 13:38.700
- He never seemed threatening?
- He's not a threatening-looking guy.

13:38.600 --> 13:43.400
I could probably take him in a fight.
He's not a convicted rapist or anything, is he?

13:43.300 --> 13:45.300
I checked.
He's got no criminal record.

13:45.300 --> 13:49.000
But you never know when one of these guys
might decide to do more than talk about it.

13:48.900 --> 13:51.300
If I went ahead with the complaint,
is this gonna mean...

13:51.300 --> 13:53.400
- a long, drawn-out court proceeding?
- It's gonna take some time.

13:53.400 --> 13:56.300
- But maybe it's worth you following through.
- What if you just talked to him?

13:56.200 --> 13:58.800
Could you figure out
if he was dangerous or something?

13:58.800 --> 14:00.700
I got his address.
I could talk to him.

14:00.800 --> 14:02.700
Maybe I could act like
an intermediate step.

14:02.700 --> 14:04.900
Oh, you know, you'd really be a doll
if you could do that.

14:04.900 --> 14:06.800
Especially if I could avoid
a big deal in court.

14:06.800 --> 14:10.000
All right, sure.
We'll go talk to this guy.

14:10.000 --> 14:14.100
Listen, Vanessa. Um, you remember
that buddy I told you about of mine?

14:13.900 --> 14:16.400
He's definitely gonna flip out
over you being here.

14:16.400 --> 14:18.800
Your buddy's gonna
be excited, huh?

14:18.700 --> 14:22.600
Vanessa Del Rio?
He's been talking about you since high school.

14:22.600 --> 14:25.200
- And what's your buddy's name?
- Manny.

14:25.200 --> 14:28.800
Manny? Little Manny?
Is that what you call it? How cute.

14:28.700 --> 14:31.300
Hey, wait a minute.
This is a real friend of mine.

14:31.300 --> 14:34.300
I believe you.

14:42.600 --> 14:45.000
This place you met
Professor Reese on Canal Street?

14:45.000 --> 14:47.200
S.O.S., right, on Canal.

14:47.100 --> 14:50.400
- That's not a gay club.
- No, it's all types. But, I mean, even so...

14:50.300 --> 14:52.300
I noticed this guy
looking all out of place.

14:52.200 --> 14:54.600
- How's that?
- Well, for one, he don't ever be dancing.

14:54.600 --> 14:57.300
This is how he would do.
He would go into the bathroom.

14:57.300 --> 14:59.400
Check you out.
Say, Do you wanna smoke a joint?"

14:59.400 --> 15:01.400
Boom. Cool. Sure.

15:01.300 --> 15:04.500
- So, he gives you one. You fire it up.
- This guy smoked dope?

15:04.500 --> 15:08.200
No, he wouldn't be smoking.
That's just like an icebreaker.

15:08.200 --> 15:10.100
Then he'd say there's
more of that at his place.

15:10.100 --> 15:12.600
- So then what would happen at his place?
- Yeah, you get high.

15:12.600 --> 15:16.000
Conversate"
till he makes his move.

15:15.900 --> 15:18.200
Then either you do
or you don't, whatever.

15:18.100 --> 15:20.900
Maybe you just smoke up
some more of his pot and then leave.

15:20.900 --> 15:24.600
- He was in this club a lot?
- Maybe once a week.

15:24.500 --> 15:27.600
But I told him this myself.
I said, What you're doing, man...

15:27.600 --> 15:31.100
this is laying yourself open
for all kinds of things."

15:31.100 --> 15:33.100
I was talking mainly about burglary,
because he had some nice stuff.

15:33.000 --> 15:36.000
But, uh, going up to somebody
in a bathroom...

15:35.900 --> 15:38.900
and it ain't even a gay club really-
that's taking a risk.

15:38.800 --> 15:41.300
- What did Mr. Reese say to that?
- Nothing.

15:41.300 --> 15:43.700
- He's just a real lonely guy. It's a shame really.
- Mm-hmm.

15:43.700 --> 15:46.900
You talked to him at all since you
hung out with him three weeks ago?

15:46.900 --> 15:50.800
- He knew I wasn't with that sex.
- You just smoke up all of his pot and then leave.

15:50.700 --> 15:54.200
- It was some good pot too.
- Just for the record, Joey, what were you doing last night?

15:58.400 --> 16:02.300
Damn. This is what I get
for coming down here to help you all?

16:02.100 --> 16:04.300
- We have to ask.
- I was with my girlfriend.

16:04.300 --> 16:06.900
Why don't you write down
the name and address.

16:11.700 --> 16:14.200
- So, I'm a suspect?
- While you got the pen there, Joey...

16:14.100 --> 16:17.500
write down the names of some of the other guys
that went to that dance club...

16:17.400 --> 16:20.900
that might have taken
Mr. Reese up on his hospitality like you did.

16:20.900 --> 16:24.500
Who may or may not have been gracious enough
to make him feel loved.

16:24.400 --> 16:26.700
- I got no way of knowing about no other guy.
- Come on, Joey.

16:26.700 --> 16:29.200
The only reason I came here
is I feel sorry for the guy.

16:29.200 --> 16:31.100
I'm being straight up with you.

16:31.200 --> 16:34.000
Does your girlfriend know you go home
with men you meet in public toilets?

16:33.800 --> 16:36.500
Yeah, I told her about it.
I took her some of the dope.

16:36.500 --> 16:39.700
All right. Calm down, Joey.
Look, I think you're being straight with us.

16:39.700 --> 16:43.400
But whatever decent impulse it was
that brought you down here...

